juju-installer (0.1.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * PoC2: Add Canonical K8s substrate support.
  * Split monolithic service into three: snap-only, LXD, K8s.
  * Add substrate detection from charm name suffix (-k8s).
  * Non-deploy commands now install juju snap only (no LXD).
  * Rewrite tests for new three-socket architecture.

 -- Ubuntu Developers <ubuntu-devel-discuss@lists.ubuntu.com>  Mon, 12 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

juju-installer (0.0.4) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add root user check: prevent running juju deploy as root (snap confinement
    blocks access to /root/.local).
  * Update design spec with root user check rationale.

 -- Ubuntu Developers <ubuntu-devel-discuss@lists.ubuntu.com>  Mon, 12 May 2026 02:30:00 +0000

juju-installer (0.0.3) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add cgroup pre-flight check to detect non-login sessions (su/sudo/lxc exec).
  * Warn users to use SSH or direct login instead of su/sudo for first deploy.
  * Update design spec with cgroup check rationale.

 -- Ubuntu Developers <ubuntu-devel-discuss@lists.ubuntu.com>  Mon, 12 May 2026 02:00:00 +0000

juju-installer (0.0.2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add timing hint to step 1/5 progress message.
  * Show 'juju status' hint after successful deploy with bootstrap.
  * Fix: use id -un instead of $USER in error message.
  * Fix: redirect service progress to stderr, fix wrapper recv protocol.

